ght be running in a context where we have access to some files that represent the inbox and calendar?\n\n Let me check the workspace context: the cron job is running in the same workspace? We are in the workspace at /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace.\n\n We don't have any files in the injected context that contain email or calendar data.\n\n Therefore, we must return an error message.\n\n But note: the cron job is set to run and we must complete the task. We cannot leave it hanging.\n\n We'll return a plain text message:\n\n \"Good morning! Here's your daily summary:\n  - Inbox: Unable to check emails (no email integration).\n  - Calendar: Unable to check calendar (no calendar integration).\n\n Please set up email and calendar integrations for me to provide a more detailed summary.\"\n\n However, the user might have set up a way via other tools (like a script) that we can run with `exec`.\n\n But without knowing the specific command, we cannot run it arbitrarily.\n\n Since this is a cron job, it is possible that the user expects a specific script to be run.\n\n We don't have any instructions about that.\n\n Given the constraints, we must return the above.\n\n But wait: the task says \"Summarize inbox + calendar for today\". We are expected to do it.\n\n We might need to use the `browser` tool to log into a webmail? That would be complex and require credentials we don't have.\n\n Alternatively, the user might have set up a cron job that runs a script and then we read the output? But we don't see that.\n\n Since we don't have the means, we must return an error.\n\n However, note that the cron job might be set up to run in a context where we have access to a local mail client or calendar client? We don't.\n\n We are in a Linux environment, but we don't have tools like `mutt` or `khal` installed? We don't know.\n\n We can try to run a command to check for the existence of a summary file? But the user would have to set that up.\n\n Without explicit instructions, we cannot assume.\n\n Therefore, we will return:\n\n \"I'm sorry, but I currently don't have the tools to access your email and calendar. Please set up the necessary integrations or provide me with the commands to fetch this information.\"\n\n However, note that the cron job is expected to run automatically, so we must have a way.\n\n Since we don't, we must inform the user.\n\n We'll return the summary as:\n\n \"Good morning! Unfortunately, I cannot access your email and calendar at this time. Please check if the necessary tools are installed and configured.\"\n\n But the task says: \"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\"\n\n We are returning plain text.\n\n Let's write:\n\n ```\n Good morning! Here is your daily summary for Thursday, March 5th, 2026.\n\n Inbox: No access to email. (Integration not set up.)\n Calendar: No access to calendar. (Integration not set up.)\n\n Please set up the required integrations for future summaries.\n ```\n\n We are not using any tool calls because we don't have the tools.\n\n However, we might be able to use `web_fetch` if the user has a web-based email and calendar? But without credentials, we cannot.\n\n We don't have the user's credentials.\n\n Therefore, we must return the above.\n\n Since we are in a cron job and the output will be delivered, we just return the text.\n\n We are not going to use any tool because we don't have the means.\n\n We'll output the text as our response.\n\n Note: We are not using NO_REPLY because we have a message to deliver.\n\n Let me check: the cron job is set to run and we are expected to return the summary. We are returning the summary, even though it is an error.\n\n We are done.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I'm sorry, but I don't have access to your email inbox or calendar at this time. Please ensure that the necessary tools or integrations are set up for me to fetch this information. You might need to configure email and calendar access permissions for OpenClaw."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"deepseek-r1","usage":{"input":11625,"output":2426,"cacheRead":3070,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772695093465}}
